formed in the United States in 2007. <em>Arch Intern Med</em> 2009;169(22):2071–2077.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1001/archinternmed.2009.440">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/20008689/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Projected+cancer+risks+from+computed+tomographic+scans+performed+in+the+United+States+in+2007&amp;author=A+Berrington+de+Gonz%C3%A1lez&amp;author=M+Mahesh&amp;author=KP+Kim&amp;publication_year=2009&amp;journal=Arch+Intern+Med&amp;pages=2071-2077&amp;doi=10.1001%2Farchinternmed.2009.440&amp;pmid=20008689">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">5.</div><div id="r5" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Morcos SK, Thomsen HS, Webb JA. Contrast-media-induced nephrotoxicity: a consensus report. Contrast Media Safety Committee, European Society of Urogenital Radiology (ESUR). <em>Eur Radiol</em> 1999;9(8):1602–1613.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/s003300050894">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/10525875/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Contrast-media-induced+nephrotoxicity%3A+a+consensus+report.+Contrast+Media+Safety+Committee%2C+European+Society+of+Urogenital+Radiology+%28ESUR%29&amp;author=SK+Morcos&amp;author=HS+Thomsen&amp;author=JA+Webb&amp;publication_year=1999&amp;journal=Eur+Radiol&amp;pages=1602-1613&amp;doi=10.1007%2Fs003300050894&amp;pmid=10525875">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">6.</div><div id="r6" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Agatston AS, Janowitz WR, Hildner FJ, Zusmer NR, Viamonte M Jr, Detrano R. Quantification of coronary artery calcium using ultrafast computed tomography. <em>J Am Coll Cardiol</em> 1990;15(4):827–832.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/0735-1097(90)90282-T">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/2407762/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Quantification+of+coronary+artery+calcium+using+ultrafast+computed+tomography&amp;author=AS+Agatston&amp;author=WR+Janowitz&amp;author=FJ+Hildner&amp;author=NR+Zusmer&amp;author=M+Viamonte&amp;author=R+Detrano&amp;publication_year=1990&amp;journal=J+Am+Coll+Cardiol&amp;pages=827-832&amp;doi=10.1016%2F0735-1097%2890%2990282-T&amp;pmid=2407762">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">7.</div><div id="r7" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Sahani DV, Kalva SP, Hamberg LM, et al. Assessing tumor perfusion and treatment response in rectal cancer with multisection CT: initial observations. <em>Radiology</em> 2005;234(3):785–792.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1148/radiol.2343040286">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/15734934/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Assessing+tumor+perfusion+and+treatment+response+in+rectal+cancer+with+multisection+CT%3A+initial+observations&amp;author=DV+Sahani&amp;author=SP+Kalva&amp;author=LM+Hamberg&amp;publication_year=2005&amp;journal=Radiology&amp;pages=785-792&amp;doi=10.1148%2Fradiol.2343040286&amp;pmid=15734934">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">8.</div><div